  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0da7\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dca \u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dba\u0dda \u0da2\u0dba \u0db4\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Pakistan won the first test match",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The visiting Pakistan team won by 4 wickets in the first Test between the two countries by defeating the host Sri Lankan team by 4 wickets.",
        "Pakistan managed to beat the target of 342 runs set by the Sri Lankan team by losing only 6 wickets. Opener Abdullah Shafiq scored an unbeaten 160 and captain Babar Azam scored 55 to upset Pakistan's victory.",
        "The Sri Lankan team, who batted first in the match, scored 222 and in reply, Pakistan could score only 218 runs.",
        "The Sri Lankan team, which played its second innings again, scored 337 runs and thus Pakistan got a target of 341 runs."
      ],
